column3: Red, Ripe and Roasted Tomato and Garlic Festival
column4: Web: https://phipps.conservatory.org/calendar/detail/red-ripe-and-roastedJoin us to celebrate two of summer’s most bountiful crops at the 13th annual Red, Ripe and Roasted tomato and garlic festival. Held on our front lawn and in the Outdoor Garden, this annual festival collects fresh local produce for the Greater Pittsburgh Community Food Bank. The event features:• Cooking demonstrations and tastings;• Biggest, smallest and ugliest homegrown tomato contests with special prizes;• Local vendors selling fresh tomatoes, garlic and other produce; • And fun activities for kids!Red, Ripe and Roasted is free to attend. By donating a bag of fresh produce for the Greater Pittsburgh Community Food Bank — which can be purchased on-site or brought from home — festival-goers will also be admitted for free to Phipps’ SUPER. NATURAL. Glass Art show and Butterfly Forest from 11 a.m. – 4 p.m. This offer applies on Sun., Aug. 27 only.Donation Tips• Fresh, local produce makes the best gift, and the Food Bank is pleased to accept donations from your own garden or from local farmers.• Donations of produce that is hardy and travels well (carrots, peppers, tomatoes and zucchini are a few examples) are especially helpful.

column3: Redcliffe KiteFest
column4: Without a doubt the most popular event on the Redcliffe Festival program, Redcliffe KiteFest features an entire weekend of non-stop family friendly entertainment. On Saturday 26 and Sunday 27 August from 9am-4pm, KiteFest will transform Pelican Park in Clontarf into the Ultimate Kids Weekend. It doesn't get any better with Paw Patrol & Trolls both live on stage both days at the Redcliffe KiteFest. And the brand new Bupa Splatt Nation makes its grand deput at the 2017 event.  Don't miss the international kite displays, Jet Ski Stunt Shows, live music, handmade markets, the famous Sesame Lane KiteFest Kidz and much more.For the best family-friendly events near Brisbane experience Redcliffe KiteFest and the 2017 Redcliffe Festival – the biggest celebration to hit the Moreton Bay Region.Please note that dogs are not allowed at this event. Thank you for your understanding.

column3: Red Bull Cliff Diving Texas, USA
column4: September 3 - Event Start: 12:00 PM // Competition Start: 2:00 PM //  Red Bull TV Live & Facebook Live: 3:00 PM // Event End: 4:00 PM (local times)--------------------------------------------The Red Bull Cliff Diving World Series will return to Texas, USA, this year for the fourth stop of the series on September 2-3! Hell's Gate at Possum Kingdom Lake will once again host the world's most elite cliff divers going into the second half of the current season.Event Start 11:00 AM // Event End: 4:15 PM (local times)This event is FREE and no tickets are needed. There is no public land for viewing and you must have a watercraft (boat, paddle board, kayak, etc.) to view the event at Hell's Gate.Due to changing forecasts daily we will update as more weather information is available via this Facebook page. Rain does not always mean cancellation so please check back daily for updates and information!From Europe, the World Series travels across the Atlantic to the visual feat of two towering cliffs, rising dramatically out of the region's first water supply reservoir, where 14 men and 8 women (including wildcard divers) will vie for victory. In a venue where Australian wildcard and World Series debutante and later overall champion, Rhiannan Iffland, thrilled the crowds in 2016 as she put in a magical diving display and upset the odds with a stunning victory.Visit our website for more information: www.redbullcliffdiving.com/texas

column3: Red Bull Flugtag Nashville
column4: Since 1992, Red Bull Flugtag (German: flight day, airshow) has made stops around the world challenging competitors to build and pilot homemade human-powered flying machines. On September 23, 2017, competitors will take the plunge off the 24-foot high flight deck on the Cumberland River and attempt to break the 258-foot distance record.The event is free to attend and open to the public. Join the conversation: @redbull #RedBullFlugtag

column3: Red Bull Cliff Diving Mostar, Bosnia and Herzegovina
column4: September 16 - Event Start: 1:00 PM // Competition Start: 1:30 PM //  Red Bull TV Live & Facebook Live: 2:30 PM // Event End: 3:30 PM (local times)--------------------------------------------Pretposljednja stanica donosi povratak na legendarni Stari most u MostaruTradicija skokova sa Starog mosta, jednog od najpoznatijih simbola Bosne i Hercegovine, seže ?ak do 17. vijeka. A elita svjetskog cliff divinga ?e ponovo demonstrirati svoje umije?e pred vatrenom mostarskom publikom, na pretposljednjoj stanici sezone 2017. Ovo je stanica na kojoj gledaoci znaju skaka?e po imenima, i gdje se gaji jednako poštovanje prema tradicionalnim skokovima, koji su svojevrsni ispit zrelosti za mostarske mladi?e, i prema finoj umjetnosti cliff divinga.Sagra?en u 16. vijeku, mitski Stari most graciozno se izdiže iznad smaragdne vode rijeke Neretve, spajaju?i dva dijela Starog grada u Mostaru. S obje strane okružen utvr?enim kulama, neosjetno se uklapa u okolinu, stvaraju?i impresivan prizor. Ovaj kameni most s jednim lukom mijenja izgled kada se posmatra iz razli?itih perspektiva.Njegov graditelj bio je Mimar Hajrudin, u?enik velikog otomanskog arhitekte Mimara Sinana. Legenda kaže da graditelj nikada nije vidio završen most, jer je otišao prije skidanja skele, nemaju?i snage da vidi da li ?e most stajati. Sultan Sulejman Veli?anstveni zaprijetio mu je odrubljivanjem glave ukoliko most padne. Most se, sa okolnim dijelom Starog grada u Mostaru, nalazi na UNESCO-voj listi Svjetske baštine, i ?esto se navodi kao jedan od najljepših mostova u svijetu.Ovjekovje?en na zastavi i grbu grada, most je žila kucavica života u Mostaru od same svoje izgradnje. Stari most je mjesto gdje je tradicija nadmetanja u skokovima duga 450 godina. Jednako koliko i most, ?uvena je i slika skaka?a koji jezdi kroz zrak sa mosta prema ledenoj i brzoj vodi Neretv### ### ### The penultimate stop sees a return to Mostar’s iconic old bridgeDiving off Stari Most, the old bridge, dates back to the 17th century, and once again the world's best cliff divers will show off their skills surrounded by a fanatical crowd of spectators during 2017's penultimate stop. This is the one stop where the locals know all the athletes by their names and where both, the traditional diving from the country's most recognizable landmark in a sort of maturity test for young men and the fine art of cliff diving are equally respected.Built in the 16th century, the iconic Stari Most gracefully arches over the emerald water of Neretva River, connecting two parts of the old town in Mostar. On both sides surrounded by fortified towers, it fits seamlessly into the landscape, creating an impressive sight. This single span stone bridge seems to look different when viewed from different perspectives.Built by Mimar Hayruddin, disciple of the great Ottoman architect Mimar Sinan, legend has it that the builder never saw the bridge completed, as he left before the scaffolding was removed, having no strength to see if the bridge will stand. Sultan Suleiman the Magnificent threatened to decapitate him if the bridge fell. The bridge is, together with the surrounding part of the Old City of Mostar, on UNESCO's list of World Heritage Sites, and is often cited as one of the most beautiful bridges in the world.Eternalized in the city's flag and coat of arms, life in Mostar has been centred on the humpback bridge ever since its construction. Iconic 'Stari Most' is a place where the tradition of competitive diving is almost 450 years old. Equally iconic as the bridge, is the image of a diver soaring through the air from the bridge towards the fast and cold water of Neretva River.More information on www.redbullcliffdiving.com/mostar

column3: Red Bull Megaloop Challenge 2017
column4: 16 kiteboarders will be challenged to show their biggest megaloops in the most extreme Dutch weather conditions, when the wind hits 30+ knots or more.=== Wind window from 1st April 2017 - 1st November 2017 ===Event will be announced 3/4 days in advance.The first 8 riders are invited. The other 8 spots are available for the best entries. Every rider can submit his video with the sickest megaloop between end of January and March 16th on www.redbullmegaloopchallenge.com. All 16 riders will be announced on the website. Wind window is open from April 1st until November 1st. Let’s get ready!Red Bull Megaloop Challenge will be organized when the weather conditions are perfect. That means: when the authorities warn to stay indoors, but the best kiteboarders only have one goal: ride hard and fly high. So if nature gives us 30+ knots of wind in the right direction between April 1st and November 1st, then make sure you are ready to come over to The Spot in Zandvoort, the Netherlands or watch live on www.redbullmegaloopchallenge.com.Video submissions open: end of January - March 16thAnnouncement of invited riders by video: March 29th / 30thWeather window: April 1st - Nov 1st 2017Location: The Spot Zandvoort, The NetherlandsWebsite: www.redbullmegaloopchallenge.com Check www.redbullmegaloopchallenge.com for more information.

column3: Red Bull District Ride 2017
column4: Back again in 2017: Red Bull District Ride!Liebe Slopestyle-Freunde: Es gilt, sich den 2. September 2017 im Kalender zu markieren.Denn nun steht es offiziell fest:Der Red Bull District Ride kehrt am 1. und 2. September 2017 nach Nürnberg zurück. Beim langersehnten Comeback des legendären Freeride-Events werden erneut die besten Mountainbiker der Welt gegeneinander antreten. Im Zentrum der Franken-Metropole wird ein einzigartiger urbaner Freeride-Parcours entstehen – in fünf verschiedenen Districts gibt es Mountainbike-Slopestyle-Tricks hautnah auf Weltklasse-Niveau zu sehen.Als Teil der FMB World Tour Diamond Series ist der Red Bull District Ride ein absolutes Highlight im Bike-Kalender 2017.Nach fünf Auflagen in den Jahren 2005, 2006, 2011 und 2014 in Nürnberg sowie in Catania/Italien (2006) hat der Red Bull District Ride einen legendären Status erlangt. Die Top-Mountainbiker treten vor einzigartiger, urbaner Kulisse an und begeistern mit ihren Tricks zehntausende Zuschauer.Für alle Updates klick hier ?  http://win.gs/2fZevU5

column3: Red Bull Air Race Porto
column4: Dez anos depois da estreia, Portugal está de volta ao calendário da Red Bull Air Race World Championship! Tal como aconteceu nas edições de 2007, 2008 e 2009, a ação decorre sobre as águas do Douro, entre as cidades do Porto e Vila Nova de Gaia - num autêntico anfiteatro capaz de proporcionar aos pilotos e ao público uma experiência única. Do ponto de vista desportivo, nenhum dos pilotos atualmente no ativo venceu a etapa portuguesa, um troféu que promete ser altamente disputado. A Red Bull Air Race criou ao longo de três anos uma relação muito especial com o público, que aderiu massivamente e transformou a corrida no mais participado evento desportivo organizado no nosso país, com um milhão de espectadores. Este ano o encontro está já marcado para o primeiro fim-de-semana de setembro e como sempre o evento é gratuito. Acompanha em RedBullAirRace.com todo o campeonato e sintoniza a Red Bull TV para os diretos das corridas. Mais informações em: www.redbullairrace.comwww.redbull.tv#RedBullAirRaceSMOKE ON!

column3: The Avett Brothers / Reds Post-Game Concert
column4: As part of Reds Post-Game Concert Series, the three-time Grammy-nominated band The Avett Brothers will be performing a LIVE concert from the field on Saturday, Aug. 26!The Reds take on the Pirates, and the concert will begin approximately 20 minutes after the game ends.Everyone with a ticket to the Reds game will have the chance to enjoy the show from this popular headlining band!The three-time Grammy-nominated band has headlined festivals all around the country with their catalogue of numerous hits off of their nine studio albums. They gained mainstream popularity after performing live on the 2011 Grammy Award show telecast with Mumford and Sons and Bob Dylan. Their most recent album, True Sadness, debuted at number 3 on the Billboard Top 200 in June of 2016, coming in behind Drake's Views and Beyonce's Lemonade. The release also debuted as the number 1 album on both the Rock and Folk charts. Their first single from that album, Ain't No Man, gave The Avett Brothers their first #1 single. Their last four studio albums all charted in the top 20 on the all-genre Billboard Top 200.

column3: Red Bull Caisses à Savon Lausanne
column4: ? Red Bull Caisses à Savon est cette course hors des sentiers battus au cours de laquelle de courageux pilotes dévalent une piste en pente raide dans des caisses à savon qu'ils ont construites eux-mêmes.? Toutes les caisses sont faites à la main et ne sont propulsées ni par de l'essence ni par du diesel mais par une bonne dose de courage, de détermination et d'esprit d'équipe. Aucune limite n'est imposée à l'imagination.? Au contraire: plus une caisse à savon est créative, plus le spectacle est amusant au départ, plus l'équipe récolte de points. Et celle qui en plus atteint le but le plus rapidement a de bonnes chances de gagner.Toutes les infos et inscriptions sur redbull.ch/caissesasavon**********************************************? Red Bull Seifenkistenrennen ist das einzigartige Rennen, in dem mutige Piloten in selbstgebauten Seifenkisten eine steile Rennstrecke runterrasen.? Alle Kisten sind handgemacht und werden nicht durch Benzin oder Diesel, sondern durch Mut, Entschlossenheit und Teamgeist angetrieben. Der Fantasie sind dabei fast keine Grenzen gesetzt. Im Gegenteil:? Je kreativer die Seifenkiste, wie lustiger der Tanz beim Start, desto mehr Punkte heimst das Team ein. Wer dann auch noch möglichst schnell im Ziel ist, hat beste Chancen auf den Sieg.Alle Informationen und Anmeldungen via redbull.ch/caissesasavon

column3: Red Bull Air Race EuroSpeedway Lausitz
column4: 2017 will see the Red Bull Air Race World Championship return to the EuroSpeedway Lausitz after a brilliant round last year.In 2016 when the pilots touched down in the 3.2km (2 mile) tri-oval racetrack, formerly known as Lausitzring, it was the pivotal sixth race of the season. This year it will represent the penultimate race!Last year Matt Hall beat local hero Matthias Dolderer to the top spot on the podium in a thrilling race watched by thousands of fans. Even though the German pilot took the World Championship in 2016 he will want to claim a win above home soil. Who will win? You'll just have to wait and see.The World Championship lands in Lausitz on 16-17 September. Get your tickets soon...

column3: Rudolph The Red-Nosed Reindeer
column4: The beloved TV classic RUDOLPH THE RED-NOSED REINDEER soars off the screen and onto the stage this holiday season. Come see all of your favorite characters from the special including Santa and Mrs. Claus, Hermey the Elf, Bumble the Abominable Snow Monster, Clarice, Yukon Cornelius and, of course, Rudolph, as they come to life in RUDOLPH THE RED-NOSED REINDEER: THE MUSICAL. It’s an adventure that teaches us that what makes you different can be what makes you special. Don’t miss this wonderful holiday tradition that speaks to the misfit in all of us. Based on the animated television special “Rudolph the Red-Nosed Reindeer” and the stage production directed and conceived by Jeff Frank and First Stage. Script adaptation by Robert Penola. Arrangements and orchestrations by Timothy Splain.
